Barely a few days after regaining his freedom, the posh 13, John Kadiya Street, Asokoro District residence of former National Security Adviser, Col. Sambo Dasuki (rtd) is back to life. Former governors, ministers and associates, who before now had developed cold feet about checking on Dasuki in DSS custody, have been paying homage to the Prince of Sokoto Caliphate. It was as if those in the opposition have just found their bearing.